##What happened to the more than 10,000 cases a day in Hubei Province? Here's what the experts say

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

From 0:00 to 24:00 on February 12,14840 new cases of coronary pneumonia were reported in Hubei Province, including 13332 clinically diagnosed cases.

Why are there tens of thousands of cases a day? What is a clinically diagnosed case? Why is the number of clinically diagnosed cases included in the number of confirmed cases published? Where do the clinical cases go? How?

Why are there tens of thousands of cases a day?

From 0000 to 2400 on February 11,1638 new cases of coronary pneumonia were reported in Hubei Province. Why did the number of new cases of coronary pneumonia rise to 14,840 on February 12?

The reason is that Hubei included the number of clinically diagnosed cases in the number of confirmed cases.

What is a clinically diagnosed case?

The General Office and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine of the National Health Commission have recently published the fifth edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan for pneumonia with COVID-19 infection, adding "clinical diagnosis" to the classification of cases in Hubei Province, so that patients can be early in accordance with the confirmed cases of standard treatment, further improve the success rate of treatment.

According to the statement of the Fifth Edition Diagnosis and treatment plan, the suspected case with imaging features of pneumonia is a clinical diagnosis case.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Furthermore, the "suspected case" criterion was revised to read: With or without an epidemiological history, suspected cases may be considered as long as the two clinical manifestations, "fever and / or respiratory symptoms" and "normal or decreased white blood cell count or lymphocyte count in the early stages of the disease" , are met. It's like a broadening of the suspect list.

According to the program, Hubei Province has recently screened past suspected cases and revised the diagnosis, according to a new diagnostic classification for new patients. In order to be consistent with the classification of cases published by other provinces in China, the number of clinically diagnosed cases in Hubei Province will be included in the number of confirmed cases to be published from today.

Why should clinical cases be included?

Zeng Guang, chief scientist of epidemiology at the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, explained to the media that "clinically diagnosed cases" are those that have not been diagnosed in the laboratory and have not yet found positive nucleic acid tests, but that the clinical symptoms "look like" .

Zeng Guang said that such "delayed positive" patients do exist, but can not be ruled out, so it is easy to spread in society. If these people are included in the new cases, they can be isolated and hospitalized, it's good for society and good for the patient. The publication of the "number of clinically diagnosed cases" into the "number of confirmed cases" is the right step, closing a transmission loophole.

Source: CCTV news

In an interview with CCTV, Tong Chaohui, an expert from the Central Guidance Group and Deputy Director of Beijing Chaoyang Hospital, said, when we see doctors and diagnose pneumonia, we can get only thirty per cent of the etiology, the remaining eighty per cent depend on clinical diagnosis. From the point of view of clinical thinking and clinician's clinical path, increasing the diagnosis of clinical cases is beneficial to clinician's judgment of disease.

Tong Chaohui pointed out that some time ago we rely mainly on nucleic acid to confirm cases. In fact, according to our clinical diagnostic criteria, there are a large number of suspected cases.

Wang Chen, president of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, told the media on February 5 that the ability to detect viral nucleic acids is improving, but the accuracy of different reagents varies, and not all patients can test positive for nucleic acids, so there are a lot of patients who look at the history of epidemiology, the history of exposure like, the clinical symptoms like, but the nucleic acid has not been confirmed, and are now classified as suspected cases, and it is recommended that such patients be present in Wuhan, should be able to be classified as clinical cases, because nucleic acid for the confirmed patients positive rate is only between 30% ~ 50% , so set up the clinical diagnosis of this file is very necessary.

Where does the clinical diagnosis case go? How to treat?

As if she should be put into isolation

According to the fifth edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan, for Hubei Province, medical personnel at all levels and in all types of medical institutions are required to immediately carry out isolation treatment after finding suspicious diseases and clinically diagnosed cases that meet the case definition, the suspected cases and the clinically diagnosed cases should be isolated separately, and the samples of the suspected cases and the clinically diagnosed cases should be collected as soon as possible for pathogen detection.

According to local media reports in Hubei, according to the requirements, clinical diagnosis cases should first go to the centralized isolation point, reached critical or critical illness should go to designated hospitals. Further etiological examination, that is, nucleic acid testing, if the diagnosis of mild, should go to the shelter hospital.

Source: China News Network Integrated CCTV News, Global Times
